qxctl - Symphony administrative spine

Usage:
  qxctl <command>

Commands:
  --help                            Print concise usage
  --version                         Print version
  doctor                            Perform local repository/admin-spine checks
  contracts                         Verify first runtime-set module contract surfaces
  modules                           List deterministic runtime modules
  modules check                     Verify contract shape for all modules
  modules metadata [--json]         Extract contract metadata for all modules
  module inspect <module-name>      Inspect a specific runtime module
  module check <module-name>        Verify contract shape for a module
  module metadata <module-name> [--json] Extract contract metadata for a module
  inventory [--json]                Emit deterministic runtime inventory snapshot
  inventory digest [--json]         Emit deterministic runtime inventory SHA-256 digest
  status [--json]                   Report consolidated administrative status
  ssiag status --tops-id UUID [--scope user|system] [--json] Read safe SSIAG status
  ssiag providers --tops-id UUID [--scope user|system] [--json] List safe provider metadata
  ssiag doctor --tops-id UUID [--scope user|system] Verify local SSIAG availability
  stav status --tops-id UUID [--scope user|system] [--json] Read authenticated STAV status
  stav verify --tops-id UUID [--scope user|system] [--json] Verify the STAV digest chain
  stav query --tops-id UUID [--scope user|system] [bounded filters] [--json] Query authorized STAV projections
  stav doctor --tops-id UUID [--scope user|system] Run authenticated STAV diagnostics
  skvi inspect --prefix PATH [--version VERSION] [--json] Inspect an exact installed SKVI engine
  skvi check --prefix PATH [--version VERSION] [--json] Check canonical SKVI index truth
  skvi propose --prefix PATH --input FILE [--version VERSION] [--json] Prepare a caller-declared proposal
  skvi project --prefix PATH [--version VERSION] [--json] Build a disposable SKVI projection
